column5: Well we went down to the Quinte Area and fished where everyone else was fishing. When we got back to the dock all we heard from everyone was how bad the fishing was. No one was catching any fish. When we opened our box the questions from other anglers were flying...where were you? How deep you fishing? What were you using? Well it seems we were using the same lures as everyone else, same speeds too, only difference we could figure was we were using Torpedo Divers... Here are a few photo's from our trip. We went 4 for 7. Thanks DT10Sam for the tips, maybe next time we can get out in the same boat
Great report and pics Vanselena  Real nice eyes you guys caught    congratulation to both of you Thanks for sharing Leechman
LOL.. nothing like a shamelss plug on a Sunday night!  Some nice fish there Vans!

Nice walleyes and great job getting them. Friday was a difficult day and I didn't get out until approximately 9:30 am which is a little late on a sunny day. Hope to see you again on your next trip up here.  Regards, Sam
Nice Eyes guys! But I'm with Irish, what were those fish doing in yer box????? Unless of course you we holding them in there to revive them??? HH
I heard bananas work a little better than the divers.  According to the pics they catch fish 3:2 when compared to divers! http://www.ofncommunity.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=25385
Hey Sam thanks for the tips, Torpedo lead to lure was crucial.
Nice eyes, congrats. Personally I found the meat changed colour, and taste, when they exceeded 3lbs at BOQ. I respect your right to eat your catch though, enjoy.
"only difference we could figure was we were using Torpedo Divers"  Wow!  I've see them but never seen them used.  Exactly how do they work better than other lead weights?
